issues.body:
Sometime recently, AWS changed the way you add permissions to SNS topic to enable CloudTrail notifications. In the earlier version, you could add AWS account ids of the principals (which were accounts provided by the AWS docs).

Now that has changed, and you need to specify the service **_cloudtrail.amazonaws.com_** as the principal.

The SNS client does not seem to have a way to do this. If I use the **add_permission** method, it is looking for account ids. How can I add a permission like below to a topic?

```
{
	"Version": "2012-10-17",
	"Statement": [{   
		"Sid": "AWSCloudTrailSNSPolicy20131101",
		"Effect": "Allow",   
		"Principal": {
			"Service": "cloudtrail.amazonaws.com"
		},
		"Action": "SNS:Publish",   
		"Resource": "arn:aws:sns:Region:SNSTopicOwnerAccountId:SNSTopicName"
	}]
}
```

thanks

